data22.household = haven::read_dta("R://mhs2022d-g/MHS2022HHD.dta")
data22.person = haven::read_dta("R://mhs2022d-g/MHS2022SPL.dta")
data22 <- left_join(data22.household, data22.person) 
original.labels = var_label(data22)

data = readRDS("data_suicide.rds")

imp_data = readRDS("imputed_data_suicide.rds")  
#imp_data = lapply(imp_data,function(x){x %>% filter(Age <= 76)})

choose.col = c("#fecc5c","#fd8d3c","#f03b20","#bd0026")

smoothed km curves

surv.var = c("AFSUICAT","AFSTPLAN","AFSTTHGT","SHAGE1")

exposure = "Agegroup"

list.plot = list()
for(var in surv.var){
  
# create survival data
surv.data = data %>%
  mutate(time = as.numeric(ifelse(!!sym(var)>=97|!!sym(var)==0, Age,!!sym(var))),
         status = ifelse(!!sym(var)>=97|!!sym(var)==0,0,1),
         status = ifelse(time > 25,0,status),
         time = ifelse(time > 25, 25, time))
         
# Weighted Kaplan-meier model
km_fit = survfit(Surv(time,status)~ Agegroup, data = surv.data, weights = weight)
km_data = data.frame(time = km_fit$time, 
                     surv = km_fit$surv,
                     lower = km_fit$lower,
                     upper = km_fit$upper,
                     agegroup = factor(rep(levels(surv.data$Agegroup), km_fit$strata), levels = c("16 to 25", "26 to 41","42 to 57",">57"))) %>%
  group_by(agegroup) %>%
  mutate(surv_smooth = predict(loess(surv ~ time)),
         lower_smooth = predict(loess(lower ~ time)),
         upper_smooth = predict(loess(upper ~ time))) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(surv_smooth = ifelse(surv_smooth>1,1,surv_smooth),
         lower_smooth = ifelse(lower_smooth>1,1,lower_smooth),
         upper_smooth = ifelse(upper_smooth>1,1,upper_smooth))

list.plot[[var]] = ggplot(km_data) + 
  geom_line(aes(x = time,y=surv_smooth,color = agegroup))+ 
  geom_ribbon(aes(x = time, ymin=lower_smooth, ymax = upper_smooth, fill = agegroup),alpha = 0.3)+ 
  labs(title = original.labels[[var]],
       x = "Age",
       y = "Survival Probability") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = choose.col, name = "Generation",labels = c("Generation Z","Millennials","Generation X", "Baby Boomers")) +
  guides(color= "none") +
  theme_minimal()
  

}

store.results = read.csv("cox_results.csv") %>% 
  mutate(agegroup = factor(agegroup, levels = c("16 to 25","26 to 41","42 to 57", ">57")[4:1]),
         var = factor(var, labels = c("First time made a plan for taking own life",
                                      "First time seriously thought about taking own life",
                                      "First attempted to take own life",
                                      "First time self-harmed")),
         variables = factor(case_match(variables, 
                               "GenDiverseFemale" ~ "Female",
                               "GenDiverseGender diverse" ~ "Gender diverse",
                               "SexorientGay/Lesbian/Bisexual" ~ "Gay/Lesbian/Bisexual",
                               "ATSIAboriginal or Torres Strait Islander" ~ "Indigenous",
                               "CALDYes" ~ "CALD",
                               "CLOSEATTYes" ~ "Someone close took/attempted to take own life",
                               "LTHYNKRHas a long-term health condition" ~ "Long-term health condition",
                               "ICD_MHHHas a lifetime mental disorder" ~ "Mental disorder",
                               "ICD_ANXHHas a lifetime Anxiety Disorder" ~ "Anxiety Disorder",
                               "ICD_AFFHHas a lifetime Affective Disorder" ~ "Affective Disorder",
                               "ICD_SUBHas a lifetime Substance Use Disorder" ~ "Substance use disorder",
                               "PT13Yes" ~ "Badly beaten as child by parents",
                               "PT22_1Yes" ~ "Witnessed serious physical fights at home when child",
                               "sexually_assaulted_before19Yes" ~ "Sexually assaulted before 19",
                               .default = variables), 
                            levels = c("Female","Gender diverse","Gay/Lesbian/Bisexual","Indigenous","CALD",
                                      "Long-term health condition","Mental disorder","Anxiety Disorder","Affective Disorder","Substance use disorder",
                                      "Someone close took/attempted to take own life",
                                      "Badly beaten as child by parents",
                                      "Witnessed serious physical fights at home when child",
                                      "Sexually assaulted before 19")[14:1]),
         group = factor(case_match(variables,
                            c("Female","Gender diverse","Gay/Lesbian/Bisexual","Indigenous","CALD") ~ "Demographics",
                            c("Long-term health condition","Mental disorder","Anxiety Disorder","Affective Disorder","Substance use disorder") ~ "Conditions",
                            c("Someone close took/attempted to take own life","Badly beaten as child by parents","Witnessed serious physical fights at home when child","Sexually assaulted before 19") ~ "Events in life"),
                        levels = c("Demographics", "Conditions","Events in life"))
         ) 

forest = list()
for(vari in levels(store.results$var)){
  
  data = store.results %>% 
    filter(var == vari) 
  
forest[[vari]] = data %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = variables, x = `exp.coef.`, xmin = `lower..95`, xmax = `upper..95`, color = agegroup)) + 
  geom_pointrange(position = position_dodge(width = 0.5), size = 0.5, shape = 18) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(y = "",x = "HR (95% CI)", color = "Generation", title = vari, fill = "") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = choose.col,
                     breaks = c("16 to 25", "26 to 41","42 to 57",">57"),
                     labels = c("Generation Z","Millennials","Generation X", "Baby Boomers")) +
  geom_rect(data = unique(data %>% select(group, variables)),
            aes(xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf,
                ymin = as.numeric(variables) - 0.5,
                ymax = as.numeric(variables) + 0.5, fill = group), alpha = 0.1, inherit.aes = FALSE)
  

}
